Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> at a high level, you buy hashrate on NiceHash, and you point that to your privately run mining pool. You secretly mine your own chain, and then unleash that onto the public network. 51% attacks are the simple infrastructure and a double spend requires lots of additional custom code and fancy stuff. Attackers spend lots of time + energy on that code and don't release that code publicly

Content: [dscrd-hush] <RunningMantheCoin> everyone . As you all know, since the Cryptopia disaster Hush has been limited to one exchange (tradesatoshi) where volumes have been fairly low. Some of the most common comments we see in this discord are the need to be on more exhanges. We have applied to every well known exchange but do not often hear back. Recently, we have been in contact with CryptoBridge who has offered to list us on their exchange (for a fee of course). Their current daily volume is around 400k USD (per CMC) which is actually only half of TradeSatoshi. If getting listed on CryptoBridge is something that we as a community would like to do, then we need to raise 2.5 BTC in order to get the listing. However, if everyone would rather wait & see if we can find a better deal at a higher volume exchange, then that is fine with us as well. If you are willing to contribute BTC to help Hush get listed on crypto Bridge, please THUMBS UP this comment. If not, please voice your opinions as such. This is a community project and we're all decision makers here. So let us know what you think!

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <RunningMantheCoin> @Francis my task has been specifically to find out what the needs are in order to get HUSH listed on exchanges. Since Hush and BTCH are seperate coins, then yes they would each need to be paid for seperately. However, the short term issue with trying to get BTCH listed is there is very little paperwork or online forums that talk about the coin. Hush has a much larger history (bitcointalk forums, huge Github, large twitter acccount, good website etc). So functionally speaking, there is a much higher chance of getting Hush listed on an exchange than BTCH simply because of the sheer work that BTCH needs in order to catch up to HUSH
